propDescriptions.boundaryCount: Number of always visible pages at the beginning and end.
propDescriptions.classes: Override or extend the styles applied to the component. See CSS API below for more details.
propDescriptions.defaultPage: The page selected by default when the component is uncontrolled.
propDescriptions.getItemAriaLabel:
Accepts a function which returns a string value that provides a user-friendly name for the current page. This is important for screen reader users.
For localization purposes, you can use the provided translations.

Signature:
function(type: string, page: number, selected: bool) => string
type: The link or button type to format ('page' | 'first' | 'last' | 'next' | 'previous'). Defaults to 'page'.
page: The page number to format.
selected: If true, the current page is selected.
propDescriptions.onChange:
Callback fired when the page is changed.

Signature:
function(event: object, page: number) => void
event: The event source of the callback.
page: The page selected.
propDescriptions.renderItem:
Render the item.

Signature:
function(params: PaginationRenderItemParams) => ReactNode
params: The props to spread on a PaginationItem.
propDescriptions.shape: The shape of the pagination items.
propDescriptions.siblingCount: Number of always visible pages before and after the current page.
propDescriptions.sx: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles. See the `sx` page for more details.

root.description: Styles applied to the root element.
